# Student Profile Update Feature

Students can currently sign up with full details, but have no way to edit those details later. This feature adds an **Edit Profile** button in the dashboard header that opens a beautiful multi-section modal. Changes are persisted to the database and the dashboard refreshes automatically.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend – student-features route

#### [MODIFY] [student-features.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/routes/student-features.js)

Add a new authenticated `PUT /student-features/update-profile` endpoint that accepts any editable student fields (Basic Info, Academic, Skills, Links, Career Preferences, Address) and saves them to the [Student](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/pages/StudentDashboard.jsx#17-379) document. Password changes are **not** handled here (that's already covered by the password-reset flow).

---

### Client – API service

#### [MODIFY] [api.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/services/api.js)

Add `updateStudentProfile(payload)` — a thin wrapper around `PUT /student-features/update-profile`.

---

### Client – New Modal Component

#### [NEW] [ProfileEditModal.jsx](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/components/student/ProfileEditModal.jsx)

A full-screen overlay modal with 6 tabbed sections (matching the [Student](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/pages/StudentDashboard.jsx#17-379) schema):

| Tab | Fields |
|-----|--------|
| **Basic** | firstName, lastName, phone, dateOfBirth, gender |
| **Academic** | department, degree, specialization, cgpa, graduationYear, currentSemester, admissionYear |
| **Skills** | add/remove skills; proficiency selector (beginner/intermediate/advanced/expert) |
| **Links** | linkedinUrl, githubUrl, portfolioUrl |
| **Career** | targetRole, willingToRelocate, preferredLocations, expectedSalaryMin/Max |
| **Address** | city, state, pincode, country |

On **Save Changes**, calls `updateStudentProfile()` then fires `onProfileUpdate(updatedStudent)` so the parent can refresh the displayed data without a full page reload.

---

### Client – Student Dashboard

#### [MODIFY] [StudentDashboard.jsx](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/pages/StudentDashboard.jsx)

- Import `ProfileEditModal` and add a boolean `showEditProfile` state.
- Add an **✏️ Edit Profile** button beside the profile completion widget in the header.
- Pass `student`, `open`, `onClose`, and `onProfileUpdate` props to `ProfileEditModal`.
- `onProfileUpdate` sets the returned student object directly in state so the header, tabs, and progress bar all reflect changes immediately.

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification (no automated tests exist for client-side features)

> Both dev servers are already running (`npm run dev` on client port 5173 and server port 5000).

1. Open `http://localhost:5173` and log in as a student.
2. Navigate to the **Student Dashboard**.
3. Click the **✏️ Edit Profile** button in the header — the modal should open.
4. Switch between all 6 tabs and verify forms populate with existing data.
5. Change **phone**, add a new **skill** (e.g. "Docker"), update **targetRole** → click **Save Changes**.
6. Verify the success toast appears and the modal closes.
7. Verify the dashboard header refreshes (targetRole badge updates immediately).
8. Refresh the page — confirm all changes persisted (data comes from DB).
9. Test validation: try saving with an invalid CGPA (e.g. `11`) → expect an inline error.
